. In fact she had grown soft.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Damn all those who wish failure upon the amazon nation.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn growled, before whistling for her stallion. Once it came to her side, she just stood there, glancing over the field. Before letting out a long war cry, strong and proud.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Long live the Amazon Nation!&quot;<br>
<br>
 Her bleeding hand rested upon the saddle of her horse, as she continued to stay there.<br>
<br>
 It was a lie to say the amazons had lost equal to Fogstones army. They hadn't lost as many..but those they lost were powerful and strong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazondelerium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon DeLerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/25/01 1:40:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=242>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/deleriuml9/images/del2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To fight the good fight, is to fight a winning battle.</span><hr size=1> ~DeL sat upon her mare the ind that Demeter brung whipping her dirt and blood splattered hair over her sirty and bloody face. Her eyes empty of emotion as she looked upon the bodies of the fallen Amazons. She sat ridig, sorrowfull, yet te only thing on her face to show her emotion ,was the frowm on her split lip.~<br>
