<br>
A few hours later, the last body, and the last soul were being taken care of. Apollo cooed in sorrow, it was such a shame what had come to pass here. Apollo then took to the skies, flying into the slightly lit sky. The stars where still shining, as was the sun. It was eerie. The earth was silent, and calm.<br>
<br>
The white dove could be seen flying into the sky. The war was done, the bodies moved, it was all over, and soon another day would dawn on Greece. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
    </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/25/01 6:28:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=244>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.tripod.com/~Poseidon64/poseidon3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: War over</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon woke to find himself spread out on a couch with his arm tightly wrapped and his head bandaged. The room was empty and glowed brightly. Great pillars and mosaics adorned the great hall he was in. Gold plated floors made of marble looked to be freshly waxed and the sofa he lay on had many soft luxuriant pillows made of warm wool. Poseidon looked at his body and saw his fair skin was bruised yet mending. He had a splitting headache and his arm was numb and felt as if it were not there. The cool, temperate air was felt good to him. Poseidon carefully pulled himself up to sit up on the couch. Then he got up slowly and groaned as he did so. His strong, weary legs carried him over to a bubbling fountain from which water poured forth from the mouth of a golden stallion reared up on its hind legs. The chrystalline water shifted in tints until the vision of what was going on down below on earth appeared. The war was over and bodies were being recovered. The wounded helped with the dead and were being helped themselves. Poseidon sighed and shook his head. The error of his ways became apparent to him. He realized descisions should be made with care and for the good of all at that very moment as he looked on the destruction below. He knelt at the edge of the round fountain and leaned over the marble wall over the churning water. He brought his hand down slowly and shakily to the water. He stopped just short of the surface and  clached his hand tightly.::<br>
<br>
'I'm sorry, sorry for it all.' <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A> at: 11/25/01 6:30:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 234<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/25/01 6:36:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=245>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: War over</span><hr size=1> ::Sartha had stopped and turned towards home as soon as she had heard the words, knowing what would come. Even Fogstone would not ignore those words. Glancing around, her silvery-golden eyes narrowed. So pointless... And home she went, back to the village. She had no reason to mourn, or to celebrate. She felt cold and numb, more than usual. Needing sleep and a medic, she started off, homeward bound:: <p>~The old days are gone. You can't live in the past, and you can't wait for the future. Now is all we have. You do the other two, you waste your life...
Sartha Anne Rose... Amazon for all time~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maialino.it/musica/bsb_nick.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/25/01 6:48:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=246>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bboysfans.tripod.com//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/cuero.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Self-regret</span><hr size=1> Apollo had just happended to land on Olympus,transforming from his bird state, to his normal greatness, when Poseidon whispered those sorrowful words to himself. Standing there for a moment, his head fell to the side. He rarely saw these moments from Poseidon. These moments of self-regret. A smile found its way onto his face, and a tear in his eye. He walked to Apollo, his brown leather sandels slapping against the gold and marble floor. He placed a hand gently on Poseidon's strong shoulder. Apollo admired the powers of Poseidon, and though in many areas his power had exceeded that of his Uncle, his uncle had experience of millenniums.<br>
<br>
As Poseidon looked back to Apollo,with shimmering water-filled eyes, Apollo smiled. He sat down next to Poseidon, bringing his knees to his chest and wrapping his arms around them. For a moment they were silent. The silence saying what words could not, until Apollo spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do not be sorry.O, trident-bearing Earth-shaker. Do not regret anything you do, for if you regret it, you are implying you were wrong. And in life, there are no wrong answers. Just ones that produce negative, and positive reactions. Though you allowed Fogstone to shake your true beliefs, the basic belief we all have, that things should be solved without fighting. You had to do, what you thought was right.If by the will of Zeus, you remember anything I've ever told you. Remember that.To always do what you think is right, no matter how wrong others may thing it is. You have to live for yourself, and no one else.&quot; Apollo smiled to Poseidon, under the large fountain. Silence fell upon the two again. Apollo's eyes fell to the floor, his hand brushing over the golden tiles.<br>
<br>
&quot;You should get some rest. I will have Hermes tell Amphitrite you will be resting here on Olympus for the night. I will have a chariot ready to take you home in the morning. Now go rest.&quot; Apollo stood up, dusting off his tunic. He smiled to Poseidon and walked off, he had many things to do and the day was growing old. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
    </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maialino.it/musica/bsb_nick.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 11/25/01 6:51:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/25/01 10:05:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=247>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The End . . . </span><hr size=1> And where was Alysia during all of this? The blow from Poseidon threw her back and she wasn't able to get up in time to dodge the rising boulders. As they came back down, two trapped her body, and she wanted to fight this the mortal way. She would stay there until she herself would be able to be removed from the ruble.<br>
<br>
She was bruised and bleeding as most of them were, she was lucky to have gone up against such a God as Poseidon and cause harm, even pain against him. <br>
<br>
But the war was over . . . and there was no true victor. The Amazons Lived on, and the Gods couldn't die. <br>
<br>
Alysia finally pushed one of the boulders over and watched it topple and break upon another below. She sat up and glanced around and the blood soaked feild. Something about this reminded her of the wars of the Tretmolec. And how soon she would remember them more clearly.<br>
<br>
She stood up and whistled for her mare. As she glanced over the horizon at her sisters leaving for home, she saw in the distance a man. A man running away from her.<br>
<br>
And with that, she mounted her horse and rode towards the mountain ridge where he was headed . . . but would she return?<br>
